So i have the following code -
```{% dnd_area "section-one", class="section-one"  %}
{% dnd_section vertical_alignment='MIDDLE' %}

        {% dnd_module "horizontal_spacer" path="@HubSpot/horizontal_spacer", offset=0, width=2 %}
{% end_dnd_module %}
        {% dnd_module path="@HubSpot/rich_text", offset=2, width=4 %}
            {% module_attribute "html" %}
            &lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Header&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
            &lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;Subhead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Content goes here&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
            {% end_module_attribute %}
        {% end_dnd_module %}

        {% dnd_module "horizontal_spacer" path="@HubSpot/horizontal_spacer", offset=6, width=6, %} 
        {% end_dnd_module %}

{% end_dnd_section %}
{% end_dnd_area %}```
when using the editor - the dnd_module "horizontal space" doesnt have any editable fields...whearas, if i have an empty dnd area AND drag in the horizontal space module - then i can click and edit the style - i realized after a few tries that using the latter method i was editing a column.... when i went back to edit the template - there is a warning that the dnd_module cannot be a descendant of a column - thoughts?
